> how to share task history to other pc

To share this work/task history to another PC, best way is:

1. Push code to GitHub/Git repo:
```powershell
git status
git add .
git commit -m "Build Slotra phase 1 backend API"
git push
```

2. On other PC, clone/pull:
```powershell
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd Slotra/backend-dotnet-api
dotnet restore
dotnet ef database update
dotnet run --launch-profile https
```

3. Share this project notes/history too:
Create a file like `docs/api-progress.md` and paste the current backend summary: Identity auth, seeded roles/users, controllers, services, remaining work, run commands.

Important: Codex chat history itself does not automatically move with the code. Git shares the actual project. For the conversation/task memory, export/copy the summary into a markdown file in the repo, then commit it.
